President Biden has declared a major disaster in Washington state due to severe winter storms, winds, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred between December 29, 2020, and January 16, 2021. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. This includes funding for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Timothy B. Manner has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.